Kung Tsui-chang Edit Profile

孔垂长, 孔垂長

philosopher

Kung Tsui-chang is the Sacrificial Official to Confucius in the Republic of China and Senior Advisor to the President of the Republic of China.

Background

Kung is the 79th-generation descendant of Confucius in the main line of descent, making him the titular head of the Kong family.
